{"title": "When high-earning women take on ex-husbands in court", "tags": "business", "timestamp": "2024-04-07", "content": "Men tend to be the main breadwinners in most families and they often fight tooth and nail to retain as much of the assets as possible in a bitter divorce. But two recent cases in Singapore show how high-earning women can fight their corner just as ferociously.\nThe women, both leading executives earning around $30,000 a month, ended up in court to stop their ex-husbands from getting more than their share of the family assets."}